# Matex External MCP Bridge Rules

## The Bridge Pattern
Every external service (Stripe, DocuSign, Onfido, carriers, etc.) is wrapped as an **MCP bridge server**. To any consuming server or AI agent, a bridge is **indistinguishable from a local MCP server**. This provides vendor independence and consistent error handling.

A bridge must:
1. Expose standard MCP tools matching the consuming server's expected interface.
2. Handle authentication, rate limiting, and retries for the external API internally.
3. Translate external data formats to Matex standard schemas before returning.
4. Publish events to the Event Bus (e.g., `stripe-bridge.payment.completed`).
5. Report all API calls to `log-mcp` (latency, status, errors, request hash).
6. Implement a circuit breaker.
7. If a fallback bridge exists, failover automatically on circuit open.

## Circuit Breaker Configuration (All Bridges)
| Parameter | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `retry_count` | 3 | Retries on transient failure |
| `retry_backoff_base` | 1 second | Base delay for exponential backoff |
| `retry_backoff_max` | 60 seconds | Maximum delay between retries |
| `circuit_breaker_threshold` | 5 | Consecutive failures to open circuit |
| `circuit_breaker_reset` | 30 seconds | Time before half-open retry |
| `timeout` | 10 seconds | Max wait for external API (30s for carriers, 60s for eSign) |

```typescript
// All bridge tool calls must wrap external HTTP calls:
await withCircuitBreaker(bridgeName, async () => {
  return await withRetry(async () => {
    return await callExternalApi(endpoint, payload);
  }, { retryCount: 3, backoffBase: 1000, backoffMax: 60000 });
});
```

## Fallback Providers
| Primary Bridge | Fallback | Trigger |
|---|---|---|
| `docusign-bridge` | `adobe-sign-bridge` | Circuit open |
| `adobe-sign-bridge` | `docusign-bridge` | Circuit open |
| `sendgrid-bridge` | Postmark bridge | Circuit open |
| `twilio-bridge` | Vonage bridge | Circuit open |
| `lme-bridge` | Cached last-known prices | Circuit open |
| `fastmarkets-bridge` | Cached last-known prices | Circuit open |
| `maps-bridge` | OpenStreetMap fallback | Circuit open |
| `onfido-bridge` | Manual review queue | Circuit open |
| `stripe-bridge` | Queue + retry (no fallback) | Never fail silently â€” queue |

Financial bridges (`stripe-bridge`) have **no silent fallback** â€” failures must be queued for retry, never silently dropped.

## Vendor Independence Rule
Bridges expose standard MCP tool interfaces so consuming servers require **zero code changes** when switching vendors. Example:

Switching from DocuSign to Adobe Sign:
1. Deploy `adobe-sign-bridge` implementing the same tools (`create_document`, `send_for_signing`, etc.).
2. Update `esign-mcp` configuration to point to the new bridge.
3. Zero changes to `esign-mcp` business logic.

## Bridge Tool Specifications

### stripe-bridge
| Tool | Stripe API |
|---|---|
| `create_payment_intent` | POST /v1/payment_intents |
| `confirm_payment` | POST /v1/payment_intents/:id/confirm |
| `create_refund` | POST /v1/refunds |
| `create_transfer` | POST /v1/transfers (Connect payout) |
| `create_customer` | POST /v1/customers |
| `attach_payment_method` | POST /v1/payment_methods/:id/attach |
| `get_balance` | GET /v1/balance |
| `handle_webhook` | Stripe webhook endpoint |

### onfido-bridge
Identity verification tools: `create_applicant`, `upload_document`, `create_check`, `get_check_result`.
On circuit open â†’ route to manual review queue (never block KYC silently).

### carriers-bridge
Wraps Day & Ross, Manitoulin, Purolator, GoFor simultaneously.
Tools: `request_quotes` (dispatches to all carriers in parallel), `book_shipment`, `track_shipment`, `cancel_shipment`.
On circuit open for a specific carrier â†’ exclude from quote results and log.

### lme-bridge / fastmarkets-bridge
Cache last-known prices with a TTL of 5 minutes.
On circuit open â†’ return cached price with `{ stale: true, cached_at: timestamp }` flag.
Never return a null price â€” always fall back to cache.

## Bridge File Structure
```
packages/bridges/<name>-bridge/
  src/
    index.ts          â€” MCP server entry, registers tools
    client.ts         â€” external API client with auth
    circuit-breaker.ts â€” circuit breaker implementation
    transformer.ts    â€” external format â†’ Matex schema mapping
    types.ts          â€” bridge-specific types
  package.json
```

## Logging Requirements for Bridges
Every external API call must be logged to `log-mcp` with category `external_api`:
```typescript
await logMcp.logExternalApiCall({
  server: 'stripe-bridge',
  endpoint: '/v1/payment_intents',
  method: 'POST',
  request_hash: sha256(JSON.stringify(payload)),  // never log raw payload
  response_status: 200,
  latency_ms: elapsed,
  success: true,
});
```
